Fix EXC_BAD_ACCESS crash in TVMFFIEnvModLookupFromImports

The crash occurs when generated Metal code calls TVMBackendGetFuncFromEnv
to look up "gemm_kernel" but the function is not found. The
TVM_FFI_THROW(RuntimeError) at line 89 of module_internal.h throws an
exception, but during exception cleanup, the error object is accessed
after being freed (use-after-free), causing EXC_BAD_ACCESS at address
0x6c616e7265746e49 (ASCII "Internal").

The backtrace shows:
  frame #12: TVMBackendGetFuncFromEnv ... func_name="gemm_kernel"
  frame #11: TVMFFIEnvModLookupFromImports (returns error)
  frame #10: __cxa_decrement_exception_refcount (exception cleanup)
  frame #9-7: InternalError::~InternalError / Error::~Error
  frame #3-2: Object::DecRef -> SimpleObjAllocator::Handler::Deleter_
  frame #0: CRASH - reading freed memory containing "Internal" string

Root cause: The error object (InternalError) allocated by
SimpleObjAllocator is being double-freed or accessed after free during
exception propagation across the libtvm_ffi <-> libtvm shared library
boundary. The ErrorObjFromStd handler's Deleter_ is called on a
corrupted/freed object.

Proposed fix: The issue is in the exception handling across shared
library boundaries. The TVM_FFI_SAFE_CALL_BEGIN/END macros in
TVMFFIEnvModLookupFromImports catch C++ exceptions and convert them to
error codes, but the exception object lifetime management fails when
the exception is thrown from one shared library (libtvm_ffi) and caught
in another.

The fix should ensure the error string is copied before the exception
object is destroyed, or use a thread-local error storage that doesn't
depend on exception object lifetime.

--- a/3rdparty/tvm-ffi/src/ffi/extra/module_internal.h
+++ b/3rdparty/tvm-ffi/src/ffi/extra/module_internal.h
@@ -85,7 +85,13 @@
       return tvm::ffi::Function::GetGlobal(s_name);
     }();
     if (!opt_func.has_value()) {
-      TVM_FFI_THROW(RuntimeError) << "Cannot find function " << name
+      // Build the error message as a std::string first to avoid
+      // lifetime issues when the exception propagates across shared
+      // library boundaries (libtvm_ffi <-> libtvm).
+      std::ostringstream oss;
+      oss << "Cannot find function " << name
                                    << " in the imported modules or global registry.";
+      std::string msg = oss.str();
+      TVM_FFI_THROW(RuntimeError) << msg;
     }
     module->import_lookup_cache_.Set(s_name, *opt_func);
     return const_cast<FunctionObj*>((*opt_func).operator->());
